  "text": "is above an empirically determined threshold, where K 0 is the number of clusters, p k is the priori probability of class k, and \u03bc i,k is the mean expression level of gene g i in class k, with Jianhua Xuan et al. corresponding standard deviations \u03c3 i,k . The weighting function, \u03c9(\u0394 i,kl ), is designed to give more weight to the proximate cluster pairs. Figure 2 depicts the \u03c9(\u0394 i,kl ) function that is defined in the following form [CITATION_1] :",
